Here's a rewritten version of the bug report in a natural tone:

"So I've got this issue with Firefox 91.0 on Windows 10 - when I use the `mask-image` property with a URL to an animated GIF (like in the snippet below or even just viewing this CodePen pen), the animation only plays if I'm actively holding down left click and dragging my mouse across the screen. The weird part is, it's not like that on Chromium, where the animation just works as expected without any fuss. So, I'm guessing this isn't supposed to happen - does anyone else see this behavior? Here's the snippet I'm talking about:

`#content { 
  width: 200px; 
  height: 200px; 
  background-color: aqua; 
  -webkit-mask-clip: border-box; 
  -webkit-mask-size: 100% 100%; 
  -webkit-mask-image: url("./mygif.gif") 
}`

